	<div id="146112" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Kristin <div class="commentdate">February  2, 2009</div></div> <div class="commentbox"><p>I love your recipes - everything I have made from your book and blog has been fantastic and many have become regulars in our house!  A couple of questions about the homemade curry powder (I have never done this but am often disappointed by store-bought blends): What variety of dried chiles do you prefer?  Do you split them open and remove the seeds or toast and grind them whole? Thank you!</p>

<p><i>HS: HI Kristin - There is a wide range of dried red chiles in the markets here, so I often use what I have on hand. I like arbol chiles, and I think the last time around I may have used smoked dried serranos.If there is any stem left, I'll lob that off, but aside from that I use them whole.</i></p></div></div>
