<p>I've been a reader forever and I absolutely love it - thanks Heidi for such an excellent and quality website.</p>

<p>For the spice issue, my mom has been doing this forever and I never realized what she was doing until recently - she would toast whole cumin seeds (maybe like a pound of it in a huge skillet) and after it cooled a bit, she would pulverize it in our blender until it would become this soft, powdery fluff. She would sprinkle this on any curry dish for a finishing smoky flavor.</p></div></div>
